        The Subscribe request message as defined by the WS-N specification. More information can be found at http://docs.oasis-open.org/wsn/wsn-ws_base_notification-1.3-spec-os.htm#_Toc133735624
        Parameters:
        subscribeRequest - A Subscribe object.
        Returns:
        A SubscribeResponse if the subscription was added successfully.
        Throws:
        org.oasis_open.docs.wsn.bw_2.NotifyMessageNotSupportedFault - Never.
        org.oasis_open.docs.wsn.bw_2.UnrecognizedPolicyRequestFault - Never, policies will not be added until 2.0.
        org.oasis_open.docs.wsn.bw_2.TopicExpressionDialectUnknownFault - If the topic expression was not valid.
        org.oasis_open.docs.wsrf.rw_2.ResourceUnknownFault - Never, WS-Resources is not added as of 0.3
        org.oasis_open.docs.wsn.bw_2.InvalidTopicExpressionFault - If any topic expression added was invalid.
        org.oasis_open.docs.wsn.bw_2.UnsupportedPolicyRequestFault - Never, policies will not be added until 2.0
        org.oasis_open.docs.wsn.bw_2.InvalidFilterFault - If the filter was invalid.
        org.oasis_open.docs.wsn.bw_2.InvalidProducerPropertiesExpressionFault - Never.
        org.oasis_open.docs.wsn.bw_2.UnacceptableInitialTerminationTimeFault - If the subscription termination time was invalid.
        org.oasis_open.docs.wsn.bw_2.SubscribeCreationFailedFault - If any internal or general fault occured during the processing of a subscription request.
        org.oasis_open.docs.wsn.bw_2.TopicNotSupportedFault - If the topic in some way is unknown or unsupported.
        org.oasis_open.docs.wsn.bw_2.InvalidMessageContentExpressionFault - Never.
